device vs entity identity discussion
One physical Sonos speaker has multiple entities in HA: media player, volume sensor, shuffle state, etc. They all share the same friendly name because they're all the same device, just different capabilities.
So the device picker needs to work at the device level not the entity level. You pick "Announcement Sonos" as a device, then PistonCore figures out which entity to use based on what you're trying to do with it. Just like WebCoRE — you picked the device, not the entity ID.
That's actually a cleaner experience AND it solves the duplicate name problem entirely. Three entries called "announcement" are three entities of the same physical Sonos speaker — in the picker you'd just see it once as one device.
This is also why the companion needs to fetch device profiles not just entity lists — the device is the thing the user thinks about, the entities are HA's internal implementation detail.
PistonCore must be 'silent' by default. Debugging data should only be generated and transmitted when a specific 'debug_mode' flag is active for a piston. Prioritize system stability over UI updates.
Pro-Tip: Make sure your Instruction File for Claude specifies: "Debug messages must be sent via the PistonCore Custom WebSocket Event, not by writing to the main HA system log." This keeps the "junk" out of the user's main logs.
